  "title": "Design Engineer (Rhino Software), Sustainable Engineering",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Conduct and complete simulations, including energy modeling, CFD analysis, and daylight studies.</li>\n  <li>Actively engage in Continuing Professional Development (CPD) to stay updated across relevant disciplines.</li>\n  <li>Manage and deliver Green Rating certification projects across various frameworks such as Green Mark and LEED.</li>\n  <li>Exhibit strong knowledge in environmental design, sustainability standards, building energy efficiency, daylight and shading strategies, sustainable systems, materials, waste management, and building physics.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor's Degree in Architectural, Civil/Environmental Engineering or related design discipline</li>\n  <li>R/Rhinoceros 3D experience is a key criteria to be suitable for the role</li>\n  <li>Proficiency in Microsoft Excel, AutoCAD, Adobe Creative Suite (Illustrator, InDesign)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If this opportunity aligns with your skills and experience, please submit your resume to <strong>koh.dickson@bayesrecruitment.com</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Dickson KOH, </strong>EA Registration R1103367</p>\n<p>www.bayesrecruitment.com</p>",
